Usage: generateTripsXml.py [options]

Options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -r DATADIR, --data-dir=DATADIR
                        give the data directory path
  -n NETFILE, --net-file=NETFILE
                        define the net file (mandatory)
  -m MTXFILE, --matrix-file=MTXFILE
                        define the matrix file (mandatory)
  -d DISTRICTFILE, --districts-file=DISTRICTFILE
                        define the district file (mandatory)
  -l, --limitlength     the route length of possible connections of a given OD
                        pair shall be less than 1.6 * min.length
  -t TRIPFILE, --trip-file=TRIPFILE
                        define the output trip filename
  -x, --odestimation    generate trips for OD estimation
  -b, --debug           debug the program
  -v, --verbose         tell me what you are doing
  -f DEMANDSCALE, --scale-factor=DEMANDSCALE
                        scale demand by
  -D DEPARTPOS, --depart-pos=DEPARTPOS
                        choose departure position: random, free, random_free
  -C, --get-connections
                        generate the OD connection directory, if set as False,
                        a odConnTables.py should be available in the defined
                        data directory
